Reasoning: The paper deals with distributed implementations of game-theoretical algorithms, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of Communicating Sequential Processes (CSP), which is a formal language for describing concurrent systems, and thus falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also deals with symmetry concepts in the context of CSP, which falls under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the problem of attaining common knowledge between processes, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of a commonly implemented version of CSP, which falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
